  <span id="freeText2111621394556962145" style="display:none">I'll be the first to admit that I didn't understand a lot of the metaphysical aspects of this book. It was recommended to me by a dutch dude that was staying at the same campground in Italy as I was. He said it was the most famous book in Holland. From what I remember, it starts with the relationship between two friends as they vie for the same woman. The woman gets pregnant by one man, and the other raises the child as his own. The undercurrent of this story is the fact that the family of one of the men were killed in concentration camps during WWII. This was a hard book go get through. Interesing...but after the last page I shut the book and said "WTF?"</span>
